<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="259">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181715" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole aculifera Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole aculifera Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculifera">Pheidole aculifera</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="259">Types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="259">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181715" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole aculifera Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole aculifera Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculifera">aculifera</taxonomicName>
, needle-bearing, referring to the long, very thin propodeal spine of the major and minor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="259">
Diagnosis A small, yellow member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group (but close to the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33712" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole diligens (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole diligens (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diligens">diligens</taxonomicName>
group) distinguished by the exceptionally thin propodeal spines of the major and minor, as well as the very low mesonotal convexity in side view in both castes; and, in the major, the exceptionally large spiracle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="259">
Similar to prostrata of Costa Rica, but easily distinguished in the major by the large spiracle, low mesonotal convexity, and presence of a rugoreticulum mesad to the eyes, as well as yellow coloration. See also the less similar boruca, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181704" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole variegata Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole variegata Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">variegata</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181707" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole violacea Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole violacea Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violacea">violacea</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="259">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.96, HL 1.00, SL 0.78, EL 0.14, PW 0.42.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="259">Paratype minor: HW 0.44, HL 0.54, SL 0.72, EL 0.10, PW 0.28.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="259">Color Major: body light reddish yellow, appendages yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="259">Minor: concolorous yellow. 1</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="259">Range Known only from the type series.</paragraph>
